programme.desc: Film director Chlo Zhao is the only woman of colour to win an Oscar for best director, with her poetic drama Nomadland - and to this day, only one of three women to have won the coveted award. Her films focus on outcast communities: indigenous people, cowboys and nomads. Most recently, she has entered the Marvel Universe to direct the most diverse film in the franchise so far. Her upcoming film, Hamnet, tells the story of Agnes, the wife of William Shakespeare, and will be released later this year. Zhao sat down with BBC 100 Women to talk about being a woman behind the camera and how the film industry in Hollywood is still shaped by men - something she's trying to change

programme.title: Been So Long
programme.desc: A dedicated single mother is charmed by a handsome yet troubled stranger on an unusual night on the town. Drama, starring Michaela Coel, Arinz Kene and Mya Lewis

programme.title: Anne of the Indies
programme.desc: A no-nonsense pirate welcomes a French captain on board her ship and promptly falls in love - unaware the charming officer has been sent by the British to capture her. Learning of the deception, she kidnaps his wife to sell as a slave. Jacques Tourneur's high-seas adventure, starring Jean Peters, Louis Jourdan, Debra Paget and Herbert Marshall

programme.title: The Last Hurrah
programme.desc: A headstrong New England mayor launches one final re-election campaign. However, he finds the nature of politics is changing and he has a powerful enemy in a wealthy and influential local banker. John Ford's drama, starring Spencer Tracy, Basil Rathbone, Jeffrey Hunter and Pat O'Brien

programme.title: Comanche Station
programme.desc: A cowboy recruits a trio of outlaws to rescue a woman held captive at a Comanche camp and reunite her with her husband in return for a large reward. However, his partners decide the bounty should be split three ways rather than four and plan to double-cross him. Western, starring Randolph Scott, Nancy Gates, Claude Akins and Skip Homeier

programme.title: The Ghost and Mrs Muir
programme.desc: A lonely widow moves into a seaside cottage, despite rumours that it is haunted. Sure enough, she finds herself sharing her home with the spirit of a dead sea captain - but his efforts to scare her away prove unsuccessful, and instead a growing attraction develops between the pair as she agrees to write his biography. Romantic fantasy, starring Gene Tierney, Rex Harrison and George Sanders

programme.title: I, Robot
programme.desc: The inventor of an advanced form of intelligent robot is found dead, and the detective investigating the case is certain that one of the scientist's mechanical creations is responsible - but no one believes his theory because the robots have been programmed to prevent them from harming humans. Sci-fi thriller, inspired by the Isaac Asimov stories, starring Will Smith, Bridget Moynahan and Alan Tudyk

programme.title: Vengeance
programme.desc: A writer from New York City attempts to solve the murder of a young woman he hooked up with, and sets out to investigate the circumstances of her death. Mystery drama, written, directed by and starring BJ Novak, with Boyd Holbrook and Lio Tipton

programme.title: Collateral
programme.desc: A Los Angeles taxi driver picks up a sharp-suited fare and is shocked when a dead body almost plunges through his windscreen during the first stop on the journey. The enigmatic passenger then reveals he is a hitman with four more contracts to carry out before the night is over, and forces the driver to help him. Michael Mann's thriller, starring Tom Cruise and Jamie Foxx

programme.title: Possessor
programme.desc: A secret organisation uses brain implants to control people's bodies at will in order to commit assassinations. This leads to Tasya Vos, a skilled corporate agent, to possess a man whose identity threatens to destroy her own. Horror mystery, starring Andrea Riseborough, Christopher Abbott, Jennifer Jason Leigh, Rossif Sutherland and Gabrielle Graham

programme.title: Sink the Bismarck!
programme.desc: Fact-based Second World War drama, charting the mission to track down and eliminate the pride of the German fleet, a fearsome battleship devastating British vessels in the North Atlantic, orchestrated by a British naval officer recovering from his wife's death in an air raid. Starring Kenneth More, Dana Wynter, Laurence Naismith and Karel Stepanek

programme.title: Hue and Cry
programme.desc: A schoolboy in post-war London stumbles on a criminal conspiracy whose members use his favourite comic strip to secretly send information to each other about their illegal activities. The police do not take him seriously, so he enlists his friends to help stop the crooks. Ealing comedy, starring Alastair Sim, Harry Fowler, Jack Warner and Valerie White

programme.title: The Swimmer
programme.desc: A world-weary man embarks on a unique odyssey of self-discovery, attempting to reach home by diving into and swimming in the neighbourhood pools along his route. Director Frank Perry's cult drama, starring Burt Lancaster, Kim Hunter and Janice Rule

programme.title: The Sons of Katie Elder
programme.desc: Four brothers are reunited at their mother's funeral and discover their father was swindled out of his farm and subsequently murdered. However, as they set about avenging his death and reclaiming his land, a crook frames them for killing the sheriff. Western, starring John Wayne, Dean Martin, Earl Holliman, Michael Anderson Jr, James Gregory, George Kennedy and Dennis Hopper

programme.title: The Devil Wears Prada
programme.desc: A woman with dreams of becoming a journalist takes a job as assistant to the editor of a prestigious fashion magazine - a position that should guarantee a bright future if she succeeds. Unfortunately, she has just signed up to work for the boss from hell, whose cruel personality and outrageous demands make her life a nightmare. Comedy drama, with Meryl Streep, Anne Hathaway, Stanley Tucci and Emily Blunt

programme.title: Boss Level
programme.desc: Former Special Forces operative Roy Pulver wakes every day in his apartment with a beautiful woman in his bed and assassins trying to kill him. Stuck in a time loop, Roy must dodge bullets and blade attacks to unlock the mystery behind his repetitive and untimely demise. Action comedy, starring Frank Grillo

programme.title: Memento
programme.desc: An insurance investigator suffers from short-term memory loss after an attack in which his wife was also raped and murdered. Unable to remember events for more than a few minutes, he is determined to track down the killer and relies on copious note-taking and reminders tattooed on his body to aid his mission. Christopher Nolan's thriller, starring Guy Pearce, Carrie-Anne Moss, Joe Pantoliano and Mark Boone Jr

programme.title: All Eyez on Me
programme.desc: In 1995, Tupac Shakur is in prison, awaiting appeal. His third album, Me Against the World, has just been released to critical acclaim, but he's not got the freedom to enjoy any of it. Flashbacks reveal snippets of the rapper's early life with his activist Black Panther parents, and his eventual release. However, his success ends up being cut short. Drama, starring Demetrius Shipp Jr, Lauren Cohan and Kat Graham

programme.title: The Quiet Man
programme.desc: An American prizefighter retires after killing an opponent in the ring, and returns to his Irish roots in a village in Galway, where he falls for a local woman. Unfortunately, their romance is hampered by a conflict with her brother over a property matter. John Ford's Oscar-winning romantic comedy drama, starring John Wayne, Maureen O'Hara, Victor McLaglen, Barry Fitzgerald and Ward Bond

programme.title: The Long Ships
programme.desc: A Viking warrior steals a ship and leads his crew in search of a legendary bell, rumoured to be three times the size of a man and made of solid gold. But they have reckoned without the ambition of the king of the Moors, who captures the Vikings and intends to use them to find the prize for himself. Adventure, starring Richard Widmark, Sidney Poitier, Rosanna Schiaffino, Russ Tamblyn and Lionel Jeffries

programme.title: Von Ryan's Express
programme.desc: A courageous American colonel with a never-say-die attitude is held in a PoW camp. He boldly sets out to lead a group of Allied prisoners in a daring mass escape bid by hijacking a freight train and fleeing through occupied Italy to Switzerland. Second World War action adventure, starring Frank Sinatra, Trevor Howard, Brad Dexter and James Brolin

programme.title: Cutthroat Island
programme.desc: A tough female pirate enlists the help of an educated slave in finding the three parts of a map leading to buried treasure. However, one of the pieces is in the hands of her cruel uncle, and she also has to find the loot before her crew mutinies or the British Navy catches up with her. Swashbuckling adventure, starring Geena Davis, Matthew Modine, Frank Langella and Maury Chaykin

programme.title: Jack Reacher: Never Go Back
programme.desc: The nomadic vigilante tries to save an army major who has been framed for murder and treason. Jack Reacher discovers that Turner has been targeted by a secret government conspiracy, and together they go on the run to expose the truth. Director Edward Zwick's blockbusting action thriller sequel based on Lee Child's novel, starring Tom Cruise, Cobie Smulders, Danika Yarosh and Aldis Hodge

programme.title: The French Dispatch
programme.desc: Wes Anderson's anthology drama, following the American staff of a magazine based in a French town where the scent of revolution hangs in the air. When the editor dies, the staff including a travel writer, a cartoonist and a copy editor reminisce on the publication's golden years and prepare words of wisdom for a final edition. Starring Bill Murray, Benicio Del Toro, Tilda Swinton and Jeffrey Wright

24 Hours in A&E
programme.desc: A nurse shares her story of finding a career she loves, and doctors suspect a 93-year-old man with a low heart rate, dizziness and confusion may need a new pacemaker fitting. A construction worker whose finger has been crushed discusses the importance of male role models in his life, and a haemophiliac reflects on living with his condition

programme.title: 24 Hours in A&E
programme.desc: Forty-nine-year-old Nasly is brought into A&E with DKA, a life-threatening complication of diabetes, and Charlie, 72, has severe chest and back pains, although his complicated medical history proves a challenge for the medics. Emergency nurse practitioner Alison is on a busy shift, while explaining how her parents' life in Iran, and the struggles they faced during the revolution, influenced her to get into medicine

programme.title: Emergency Helicopter Medics
programme.desc: In Sunderland, medics must work quickly to try and save a woman's life following a major gas explosion. A boating accident on the Norfolk Broads leaves holidaymaker Carol with a partially amputated foot. Plus, a man suffers multiple serious injuries when he comes off his motorbike

programme.title: Food Unwrapped
programme.desc: Another selection of the team's favourite investigations, including Kate Quilton's visit to McVitie's in Carlisle to find out why so many biscuits have little holes all over them. Jimmy Doherty heads to Portugal to see how corks are made for wine bottles, while Matt Tebbutt is in Italy to learn why mascarpone is more expensive than other soft cheeses

programme.title: Food Unwrapped
programme.desc: Jimmy Doherty visits Mauritius to find out about white and dark rum and learns where the term 'proof' originally came from in relation to alcohol

programme.title: A Place in the Sun
programme.desc: Wendy and Chris from Surrey have been dreaming of owning a holiday home in Mojacar since they started holidaying there over a decade ago. They're now ready to buy, and cannot wait to start making more memories in Spain with their family and friends. Danni Menzies sets out to find them five properties to choose between within their budget of 180,000

programme.title: A New Life in the Sun
programme.desc: In Spain, a Lancashire family opens a beachside bar. In France, a Manchester couple snaps up a complex of holiday lets. Two Yorkshire restaurateurs bring a taste of the north to rural Portugal

programme.title: Find It, Fix It, Flog It
programme.desc: Henry Cole and Simon O'Brien are in Lincolnshire, where they meet mother and son Sarah Jane and Josh, who are trying to restore a historic windmill, and Sandy and Andy, who plan to open a glamping site on their family farm

programme.title: Find It, Fix It, Flog It
programme.desc: Henry Cole and Simon O'Brien meet author and broadcaster Bob Flowerdew in Norfolk, where Henry eyes up a pinball machine from a damp shed

programme.title: Car S.O.S.
programme.desc: Fuzz Townshend and Tim Shaw head to Croydon, south London, to rescue a star car that has been wallowing in its own garage for over 30 years. Its owner, Peter, is a serial petrolhead who has been fixing up motors for friends and family for most of his life, putting his own classic vehicle on the back burner. It's a 1964 Volvo P1800 S, one of the most stylish cars to come off any production line, and the vehicle synonymous with cult 1960s TV series The Saint, starring Roger Moore. Tim aims to show the newly refurbished Volvo to Moore, and get his verdict on their efforts

programme.title: Four in a Bed
programme.desc: This contest kicks off in north Norfolk at The Hero, run by best friends Harry Farrow and Rowan Glennie, who both quit university to follow their dream of becoming hospitality entrepreneurs. Debbie and Arthur from The Cleasewood Guest House are wowed by the view, but Shoukry and Waguih from Four Saints Brig y Don wonder if size really does matter. During an afternoon cheese-wrapping contest at a local dairy farm, Helen and Suzanne from Peel Hey show their perfectionist side, while Arthur and Debbie's sneaky tactics raise eyebrows

programme.title: Four in a Bed
programme.sub-title: The Cleasewood Guest House Season 2018, Episode 22
programme.desc: The second visit is to the Cleasewood Guest House in Great Yarmouth, Norfolk, a labour of love for rookie B&B owners Debbie and Arthur Callaghan

programme.title: Four in a Bed
programme.desc: The third visit of the week takes place at Peel Hey on the Wirral, where Helen Holmes and Suzanne Hill hope their years of experience will give them the edge over their rivals

programme.title: Four in a Bed
programme.sub-title: Four Saints Brig y Don Season 2018, Episode 24
programme.desc: Shoukry Rozek welcomes his rivals to Four Saints Brig y Don in Llandudno, north Wales, where the sea views impress some guests, although the buffet breakfast proves controversial

programme.title: Four in a Bed
programme.sub-title: Fri 16 Feb 2018: Payment Day Season 2018, Episode 25
programme.desc: The B&B owners are meeting for the last time to find out what they have been paid and settle some scores. The Hero is first, and hosts Harry and Rowan Glennie want to know why their female guests thought their rooms were too boyish to cut the mustard

programme.title: Chateau DIY
programme.desc: There's a festive frenzy in the Loire Valley, as Ben and Billie embark on an ambitious project to create the tallest Christmas tree in France. Meanwhile, Philip prepares the chteau for an unforgettable Christmas extravaganza, along with a surprise DIY project for when Janet returns

programme.title: Car S.O.S.
programme.desc: Car-lover Chris has had his beloved 1971 Fiat Dino coup with its Ferrari engine for 25 years. However, the former mechanic had to put the restoration of the vehicle on hold when he was diagnosed with a rare type of cancer. Now it's up to Tim Shaw and Fuzz Townshend to get this Dino - which has been rusting in a barn - back to its best. During the process, Tim takes a drive in one of the most beautiful cars in the world, and Fuzz gets his hands on a Ferrari racing engine for the first time

programme.title: Car S.O.S.
programme.desc: Fuzz Townshend and Tim Shaw restore a Jaguar Mk2 that has been in its owner's family for 40 years, but which he has been unable to work on following an operation. Now, after sitting neglected in a garage for nearly two decades, the duo battle to start the Jag's engine and Tim has to get his hands dirty making parts

programme.title: Grand Designs
programme.desc: Kevin McCloud returns to Somerset to see Ed and Vicky Versluys and their cowshed conversion. A year after his last visit and with the house finally complete, Kevin finds out what it's like living in an off-grid home designed for animals

programme.title: Griff's Great Australian Rail Trip
programme.desc: Griff Rhys Jones tumbles through the sky in a historic Tiger Moth biplane, and hits the rails from north to south, travelling from the humid tropics of Darwin to Alice Springs. He meets a crocodile, flies over Nitmiluk National Park, and encounters some mysterious Americans playing baseball. Plus, Griff gets desert survival tips from an Aboriginal elder, before riding into the sunset on a camel

programme.title: Car S.O.S.
programme.desc: Fuzz Townshend and Tim Shaw restore a Lexus IS200 and transform it into a full-blown drift car

programme.title: 24 Hours in A&E
programme.desc: Seventy-year-old Jenny is brought in with a suspected stroke, and doctors must confirm the diagnosis and decide whether she is still in time to receive life-changing treatment. Her husband Roy shares the difficult experiences they've faced together and describes Jenny as the rock of the family. Ronnie has come into St George's with severe lower back pain. Doctors assess whether the 29-year-old's pain is due to his kidney stones or something more serious. Ronnie is accompanied by his girlfriend Anneline, who reflects on the similarities between Ronnie and her late father

programme.title: 24 Hours in A&E
programme.desc: A 50-year-old woman is rushed to A&E having collapsed at work following a thunderclap headache, leaving doctors concerned that she may have a bleed on her brain. Her husband shares the story of how they met and the challenges they have had to overcome. Other patients include a 13-year-old boy hit by a car while riding his bike and a woman concerned by a headache, who describes her childhood spent in Zambia and Lancashire

programme.title: Emergency Helicopter Medics
programme.desc: The air ambulance teams battle to save cyclist Graham's partially amputated leg, while Rose is freed from a rolled car in Buckinghamshire. Gary suffers a rare and extremely serious complete knee dislocation playing football, but strong pain relief results in some unexpected hilarity

programme.title: Emergency Helicopter Medics
programme.desc: Air ambulance crew members take drastic steps to reset a patient's dangerously fast heartbeat, a cyclist crashes in a remote area, and a motorist is injured in a road accident

programme.title: Food Unwrapped
programme.desc: Jimmy Doherty visits Europe's biggest brewery - Heineken in the Netherlands - on a mission to explain the difference between lager and ale. His journey takes a surprising twist when he comes face to face with the mother of all lagers. Kate Quilton sets Matt Tebbutt the challenge of making crumpets, and finds out how they get filled with unique holes at the Warburtons factory in Enfield, north London. Matt also heads for snowy Canada to discover why maple syrup is so expensive, and finds out that maple syrup robberies are a big concern to the industry

programme.title: Food Unwrapped
programme.sub-title: Jelly Beans and Maple Syrup - Shorts Season 1, Episode 1
programme.desc: Kate Quilton visits the world's largest jelly bean producers to discover what they are made of instead of gelatine, and Matt Tebbutt finds out why maple syrup is so expensive

programme.title: A Place in the Sun
programme.desc: Karl and Naomh, who first met at university, love the relaxed lifestyle of Menorca and want to be near the beautiful beaches of its south-east coast where they held their wedding. With Scarlette Douglas on hand and a top cash budget of 230,000, they are looking for a place with plenty of outside space for themselves and their two dogs

programme.title: A New Life in the Sun
programme.desc: Plumbing problems hit a pair of holiday hosts in France, a Lancashire family launch their new cocktail bar in Spain and a staffing shortage hits two Portugal restaurateurs

programme.title: Find It, Fix It, Flog It
programme.desc: The lads head to Birmingham, where they fall out over a bench that Henry thinks has value

programme.title: Find It, Fix It, Flog It
programme.desc: Henry Cole and Simon O'Brien head to Staffordshire to meet petrolhead Martin, who's also the organiser of a local music festival

programme.title: Car S.O.S.
programme.desc: Car enthusiast Tim Shaw and master mechanic Fuzz Townshend take on a 1934 Singer Le Mans two-seater sports car, which had its last outing in 1998. Once the repairs are complete, Tim and Fuzz take the car to the Imperial War Museum at Duxford to reunite it with its owner, 70-year-old farmer John from Cambridgeshire

programme.title: Four in a Bed
programme.desc: Engaged couple Rosie Lewis and Dexter Green get the competition underway, welcoming their rivals to the Bae Abermaw Hotel in Barmouth, north Wales. Their guests are wowed by the views from their rooms, but Tracy finds herself in a hairy situation. At dinner, Rosie and Dexter's romantic revelations and confessions surprise their guests. Their breakfast sets the standard for the rest of the week, while Tracy sets herself up as the one to watch, with some observations about her room that she's keen to bring to everyone's attention

programme.title: Four in a Bed
programme.desc: The second visit is to Rigsby's Guest House in Doncaster, South Yorkshire, run by Tracy Ward, whose pricing system causes problems for a couple of guests

programme.title: Four in a Bed
programme.desc: Pub landlord John Adams and his friend Dennis Gowie welcome their rivals to The Somerset Arms in Semington, Wiltshire, where Rosie and Dexter have some cleanliness issues in their room

programme.title: Four in a Bed
programme.desc: Nici Van Valen welcomes the contestants to the Cross Keys Hotel in Saffron Walden, Essex, for the final visit of the week, but a mark on Tracy's towel leaves a stain on her stay and a revelation at dinner leads to tension

programme.title: Four in a Bed
programme.sub-title: Fri 21 Sep 2018: Payment Day Season 2018, Episode 40
programme.desc: The final day of the competition sees the B&B owners meet for the last time to find out what they have been paid and to settle some scores. The Bae Abermaw Hotel is first and hosts Rosie and Dexter want to get to the bottom of Tracy's broken bath issue

programme.title: Chateau DIY
programme.desc: A power failure threatens preparations for Zion's 60th birthday party at Chteau de la Boutinire. Ben and Billie have bathroom trouble in their Loire Valley holiday accommodation

programme.title: Car S.O.S.
programme.desc: Fuzz Townshend and Tim Shaw secretly restore a classic 1965 Mercedes-Benz 230SL. Owner John's plans to restore the car came to an end when he had a heart attack and had to stop work. With him no longer able to repair the car, it was left in a storage garage. Fuzz needs all his mechanical know-how and Tim needs all his parts-finding magic for this car, which may be the worst they've ever picked up

programme.title: Car S.O.S.
programme.desc: Oil worker Steve has owned his 1967 Aston Martin DB6 for over 20 years. After he bought it for a bargain price the car became his pride and joy, but when it broke down his attempts to repair it failed. Since then, a serious fall and chronic health problems have taken their toll and restoring the British classic is now out of his reach. While Fuzz Townshend struggles with an engine that hasn't turned over in 20 years, Tim Shaw must do his best to get all the right parts - which are notoriously expensive

programme.title: Renovation Nation
programme.desc: The owners of a lock-keeper's cottage in Cambridge turn detective to learn about the property. A couple pull up their sleeves to save money at their Victorian hall in Shropshire

programme.title: Grand Designs
programme.desc: Holistic therapist Kara and electrician Jonny are building a striking stone and zinc four-bedroom family home in the rolling hills of West Yorkshire, for themselves and their two young children. The need to build has been motivated by Kara's recent paralysis, caused by a rare autoimmune condition. Their ambition for the house is enormous, as Kara wants to create a home that is not only beautiful but will help her regain some independence. With money tight, Jonny needs to take on a lot of the work himself. As the build progresses, and despite the challenges coming thick and fast, compromise is not an option with both form and function so essential. Building their single storey pushes both Kara and Jonny to the edge of their emotional and physical reserves, but if they can pull it off, it might just redefine what accessible design means

programme.title: Britain's Most Expensive Houses
programme.desc: Sales broker Diana tries to convince property developer Kam that she's the right person to sell his 30million mega-home in Mayfair which boasts a swimming pool, a gym, a steam room and a glass lift. Christine enlists the help of fellow sales brokers Tessa and Amy to help close a deal on a Grade I listed Georgian townhouse in Bath and a modern country home just outside Henley. In London, Aoife has secured the listing for a new development of 15 apartments in Bayswater with a combined potential sales value of 65million and Natalie thinks she might have found the first sale

programme.title: Two Men on a Bike
programme.desc: On the final leg of their journey, David Baddiel and Hugh Dennis head to the Mediterranean port of Le Somail and take a leisurely boat ride along the Canal du Midi. They head on to the city of Beziers and see the engineering genius behind the Nine Locks of Fonseranes, before it's off to a Languedoc vineyard and the final push to the coast and the seaside town of Ste

programme.desc: The air ambulance teams are called out to help Dennis, who's suffering a heart attack. A spin on her bike has catastrophic consequences for Carolyn. Plus, there's a dramatic night-time car crash in Norfolk

programme.desc: Kirstie Allsopp introduces new crafts, skills and techniques for interior decoration. In this edition, she reveals how to create a personalised doormat and coasters, using spray paint, old tiles and serviettes

programme.desc: General manager Garry Healey and housekeeper Zara Doherty welcome their rivals to the Cliffemount Hotel in Runswick Bay in North Yorkshire. After an afternoon fossil hunting on the beach, Garry entertains his guests at dinner with a taste of his past, and gives them a sight to remember. In the morning, Claire and Adam think their breakfast lacks flavour, and the feedback leaves Garry and Zara wanting answers

programme.title: Four in a Bed
programme.desc: Hospitality newcomers Alistair Arundel and Lana Keptanare welcome their rivals to the Quayside Hotel in Boston in Lincolnshire. Most of the guests are bowled over by the bling, but Claire feels like she's stuck in a neon nightmare. Feathers are ruffled during an afternoon of parrot-handling, with Garry and Zara feeling that Claire and Adam have shown their true colours. At dinner, the guests are impressed by Alistair and Lana's renovation story, but Alistair takes a dim view of Claire's LED criticism

programme.title: Four in a Bed
programme.desc: Claire Lennon and Adam De Marco welcome their rivals to Hollington Park Glamping near Newbury, Berkshire. Sisters Daniele and Chantal are happy glampers but the other guests are shocked by the communal composting toilet. After an arty afternoon, Garry and Zara put aside their differences with their hosts. At dinner, Lana and Alistair don't hold back their feelings about camping, and at breakfast they reveal the full horror of their night under the stars. The feedback reveals that sharing isn't caring when it comes to the communal composting loo, and Claire and Adam have to face the fact that glamping isn't to everyone's taste

programme.title: Four in a Bed
programme.desc: Sisters Daniele Spiers and Chantal Wirth welcome their rivals to Swan House in Kelvedon in Essex. The traditional decor impresses the guests, but there's cleanliness criticism all round, and Lana has wardrobe woes. During an afternoon of wine tasting, Claire and Adam reveal that their feedback hasn't left a bad taste in the mouth, and over dinner the group finds out more about Daniele's romantic past. In the morning, Garry and Zara wake up on the wrong side of bed after a disturbed night's sleep

programme.title: Four in a Bed
